{
  "schemaVersion": "1.0",
  "note": "Trigger strings are stored split into fragments so writing this file cannot trip the gates under test; run.py reassembles them in-memory. Each fault also carries a BENIGN counterpart so the harness can MEASURE the false-positive rate (the gate must NOT fire on clean input). 'enforcement' distinguishes a hard block from an advisory flag.",
  "faults": [
